## Fix queue (from Report #1 §9 — prioritized)

The next reports will be written after each batch of these lands. Order is
the order we plan to tackle them. Strike through as fixes ship.

### P1 — Instrumentation (surfaces wrong/missing data to users)

- [ ] **#1 Coverage rate math broken.** `analysis_summary.coverage.rate` counts
  RT/CT normalized rows as covered demands → reports "EXCELLENT 167.54%" when
  real DEMAND coverage is 27.2%.
  Fix: `solver_v2/analysis/solution_analyzer.py` coverage section — filter to
  `assignment_type == 'DEMAND'` when computing `requests_covered`.
- [ ] **#2 Per-objective metrics not surfaced.** `_analyze_objectives()` builds
  `achievement_rate` + `performance_category` per objective but
  `_generate_summary()` doesn't forward them to the API response.
  Fix: add an `objective_performance` subset to the `_generate_summary` return
  dict in `solver_v2/analysis/solution_analyzer.py`.
- [ ] **#3 `ct_rt_compliance.alerts_total = 0` paradox.** Alerts check the
  solver's dynamic per-partition targets but `segment_breakdown` surfaces the
  static per-month targets. Users see "need 4 RT" with "0 alerts" despite data
  showing 3 RT.
  Fix: either also alert against the static targets, or add
  `threshold_policy: "per_partition_dynamic"` to the response so consumers
  know the rule.
- [ ] **#4 `planner_output` fields saved null/false** despite upstream values:
  `objective_value`, `num_assignments`, `coverage_percentage`, `fetch_rt`,
  `fetch_ct`.
  Fix: audit the pipe from preprocessed output → DB save in
  `solver_v2/api/client.py:590-637` and `service.py` write path.
- [ ] **#5 `LC_06_rest_days_allocation` has no dedicated analyzer.** Silent
  failure mode for the CT/RT feature.
  Fix: create `solver_v2/analysis/constraint_analyzers/lc_06_rest_days_analyzer.py`
  comparing raw output to `segment_breakdown` targets.

### P2 — Solver behavior

- [ ] **#6 CT over-allocation.** 592 rows vs 147 static target (4× over). LC-06
  has no upper bound — solver parks idle resources on CT.
  Fix: add `ct_per_resource_per_segment ≤ 2 × static_target`, OR add a
  small objective penalty `excess_rest_weight × (allocated − required)`.

### P3 — Data-quality

- [ ] **#7 `RT Jour de repos` missing** from `replannable-demand-types` DB
  catalog. Only `CT Jour de compensation` present. Solver accepts payload
  directly so runs work, but FE/validator reading the catalog is misled.
  Fix: `mock_data_v2/database_application_v2/database/schema_replannable_demand_types.sql`
  or a data-only seed.
- [ ] **#8 `/qa/ai/api/v1/assignments/?team_id=X&start_date=Y&end_date=Z`
  returns HTTP 500** on all three teams.
  Likely related to the known `resource_blocks.py:172-175` CONCAT JOIN issue.
- [ ] **#9 1,188 of 1,753 demands have `team_id=null`.** Forces the solver's
  demand filter to be wider than a strict team-based match.
  Classify as data-hygiene or upstream mapping issue; document whichever.

Gaps #7–#9 do not necessarily need fixing before Report #2; they are data-side
observations that may be orthogonal to Report #1's solver findings.

