## What NOT to change between reports

- The payload (scope, teams, dates, replannable types, time limit, lock flags).
- The three teams `[7557, 7566, 7549]` and their 49 resources (size drift
  across runs is expected — document if any team's `total` changes).
- The verification methodology (same constraint checks, same cross-analysis).
- The report section order (Executive / Run / Baseline / Input / Accuracy /
  Objectives / Analyzers / CT-RT Deep Dive / Findings / Appendix).

If any of the above must change, start a new numbering branch — e.g.
`holistic_report_02a-…md` for a deliberate scope change — rather than
silently drifting.

